{"title_page": "Ramson Zhuwawo", "text_new": "{{short description|Zimbabwean footballer}}\n{{EngvarB|date=May 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Ramson Zhuwawo\n| image = \n| fullname = Ramson Zhuwawo\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1983|11|03|df=yes}} \n| birth_place = [[Harare]], Zimbabwe\n| height = {{height|m=1.74}}\n| currentclub = [[AmaZulu F.C.]]\n| clubnumber = 38\n| position = [[Defensive midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = Eiffel Flats Kadoma\n| years1 = 2005 | years2 = 2006\u20132007 | years3 = 2008\u20132010 | years4 =2010\u20132013 | years5 =2014\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[Eiffel Flats Kadoma]] | clubs2 = [[Dynamos (Zimbabwe)|Dynamos FC]] | clubs3 = [[Gunners F.C.]] | clubs4 =[[AmaZulu F.C.]] | clubs5 =[[Chicken Inn]]\n| caps1 =  | goals1 =  | caps2 =  | goals2 =  | caps3 =  | goals3 =  | caps4 = 43 | goals4 = 1\n| nationalyears1 = 2009\u2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]]<ref>{{NFT player|pid=33645}}</ref>\n| nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate = 15 November 2012\n}}\n\n'''Ramson Zhuwawo''' (born 3 November 1983 in [[Harare]]) is a [[Zimbabwe]]an soccer player who plays for [[AmaZulu F.C.|AmaZulu]] in the South African [[Premier Soccer League]].\n\n==Career==\nHe was named 2009 Zimbabwe [[Soccer Star of the Year]].\n\n==International career==\nZhuwawo made his senior international debut for the [[Zimbabwe national football team]] at the [[2009 COSAFA Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|author=Stokkermans, Karel|title=COSAFA Cup 2009|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/cosafa09.html|date=6 November 2009}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{AmaZulu}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zhuwawo, Ramson}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Harare]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean footballers]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwe international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Dynamos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:AmaZulu F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Chicken Inn F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in South Africa]]\n\n\n{{Zimbabwe-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=May 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Ramson Zhuwawo\n| image = \n| fullname = Ramson Zhuwawo\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1983|11|03|df=yes}} \n| birth_place = [[Harare]], Zimbabwe\n| height = {{height|m=1.74}}\n| currentclub = [[AmaZulu F.C.]]\n| clubnumber = 38\n| position = [[Defensive midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = Eiffel Flats Kadoma\n| years1 = 2005 | years2 = 2006\u20132007 | years3 = 2008\u20132010 | years4 =2010\u20132013 | years5 =2014\u2013\n| clubs1 = [[Eiffel Flats Kadoma]] | clubs2 = [[Dynamos (Zimbabwe)|Dynamos FC]] | clubs3 = [[Gunners F.C.]] | clubs4 =[[AmaZulu F.C.]] | clubs5 =[[Chicken Inn]]\n| caps1 =  | goals1 =  | caps2 =  | goals2 =  | caps3 =  | goals3 =  | caps4 = 43 | goals4 = 1\n| nationalyears1 = 2009\u2013\n| nationalteam1 = [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]]<ref>{{NFT player|pid=33645}}</ref>\n| nationalcaps1 = 4 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate = 15 November 2012\n}}\n\n'''Ramson Zhuwawo''' (born 3 November 1983 in [[Harare]]) is a [[Zimbabwe]]an soccer player who plays for [[AmaZulu F.C.|AmaZulu]] in the South African [[Premier Soccer League]].\n\n==Career==\nHe was named 2009 Zimbabwe [[Soccer Star of the Year]].\n\n==International career==\nZhuwawo made his senior international debut for the [[Zimbabwe national football team]] at the [[2009 COSAFA Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[RSSSF]]|author=Stokkermans, Karel|title=COSAFA Cup 2009|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesc/cosafa09.html|date=6 November 2009}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{AmaZulu}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zhuwawo, Ramson}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Harare]]\n[[Category:Zimbabwean footballer