angers]]\n| youthyears3 = 2018\u20132019\n| youthclubs3 = [[Dundee United]]\n| years1 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs1 = [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]\n| caps1 = 0\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[East Kilbride F.C.|East Kilbride]] (loan)\n| caps2 = \n| goals2 = \n| years3 = 2018\u20132019\n| clubs3 = [[Dundee United]]\n| caps3 = 0\n| goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2019\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[Tayport F.C.|Tayport]] (loan)\n| caps4 = \n| goals4 = \n| years5 = 2019\u20132020\n| clubs5 = [[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n| caps5 = 3\n| goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2019\u20132020\n| clubs6 = \u2192 [[Rossvale F.C.|Rossvale]] (loan)\n| caps6 = \n| goals6 = \n| nationalyears1 = 2017\n| nationalteam1 = [[Scotland national under-16 football team|Scotland U16]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 2\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2019-\n| nationalteam2 = [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe U23]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 2\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| club-update = 22:51, 11 April 2020 (UTC)\n| ntupdate = 10:17, 10 August 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n\n'''Mati Zata''' (born 23 June 2000) is a Zimbabwean footballer [[Midfielder (association football)|midfielder]] who last played for [[Scottish League One]] club [[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]].\n\n==Early life==\nZata, originally from [[Zimbabwe]], moved to Scotland at 4 years of age, living in [[Alloa]], Scotland with his family. He has represented his country of [[Zimbabwe]] at [[Zimbabwe national football team|under-23 level]].\n\n==Club career==\n===Alloa Athletic===\nZata joined the youth system at [[Alloa Athletic]] in 2012. He and made his under-20s debut for the club before his 13th birthday. Zata's footballing ability quickly caught the eye of Scottish Premier league club [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] after only a year at [[Alloa Athletic]].\n\n===Rangers===\nIn 2013, he joined Rangers, scoring 24 goals in his first year as a midfielder at the club. Zata quickly established himself as an important member of the Rangers youth Academy. During his time at Rangers, Zata was called up to represent the Scottish National Team under 16s. Zata earned a 2-year scholarship whilst at the club at 16 years old and also went on loan to lowland league club [[East Kilbride F.C.|East Kilbride]] to gain valuable first team experience.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/local-sport/rangers-kid-mati-zata-i-11121210|title=Rangers kid Mati Zata: \"I want to make a name for myself at East Kilbride\"|first=Paul|last=Thomson|date=7 September 2017|website=dailyrecord}}</ref>\n\n===Dundee United===\nIn 2018, Zata joined [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]] on an 18-month contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/dundee-united-sign-former-rangers-12092095|title=Dundee United sign former Rangers youngster Mati Zata|date=26 February 2018|website=Daily Record|accessdate=29 August 2019}}</ref> During this time Zata captained the reserve side to victory in the Oban Cup. Zata earned his debut in a [[2018&ndash;19 Scottish Challenge Cup]] tie with [[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone under-20s]], making a substitute appearance after only two minutes. Zata earned praise from the club's supporters after his debut match due to his combative style in midfield which helped the team come from behind to win the match 3\u20132.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dundeeunitedfc.co.uk/news/5739/ZATA-ZONES-IN-ON-GREATER-INVOLVEMENT.html|title=Zata zones in on greater involvement|website=Dundee United Football Club|date=16 August 2018|accessdate=29 August 2019}}</ref> Zata made his second appearance for the club in a 1\u20131 draw against [[Alloa Athletic]] in the same competition.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.eveningtelegraph.co.uk/fp/long-term-injury-makes-dundee-united-captains-heart-fonder-for-the-game/|title=Long-term injury makes Dundee United captain's heart fonder for the game|newspaper=Evening Telegraph|date=12 September 2018|accessdate=29 August 2019|first=Tom|last=Duthie}}</ref> He joined [[Tayport F.C.|Tayport]] on loan in March 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dundeeunitedfc.co.uk/news/5978/MATI-ZATA-LOANED-TO-TAYPORT-JFC.html|title=Mati Zata loaned to Tayport JFC|date=2 March 2019|website=Dundee United Football Club|access-date=29 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Dumbarton ===\nZata signed for [[Scottish League One]] club [[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]] in July 2019, having scored the winner against former club Dundee United whilst playing as a trialist.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dumbartonfootballclub.com/news/?mode=view&id=4089|title=SONS SIGN FOUR|last=Fullarton|first=Donald|date=11 July 2019|website=Dumbarton Football Club|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> He played just ten minutes of league football for the club before joining [[SJFA West Region Premiership]] side [[Rossvale F.C.|Rossvale]] on loan in November 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dumbartonfootballclub.com/news/?mode=view&id=4206|title=PLAYERS GO OUT ON LOAN|last=Galloway|first=Andy|date=22 November 2019|website=Dumbarton Football Club|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> While at Rossvale, he was the target of alleged racial abuse during a match against [[Rutherglen Glencairn F.C.|Rutherglen Glencairn]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gallacher |first1=Liz |title=Racist abuse hurled at teen player with Bishopbriggs junior football team from terraces |url=https://www.kirkintilloch-herald.co.uk/sport/football/racist-abuse-hurled-at-teen-player-with-bishopbriggs-junior-football-team-from-terraces-1-5069941 |accessdate=2 February 2020 |work=Kirkintilloch Herald |date=3 January 2020 }}</ref> Dumbarton's extensive injury problems led to the club recalling Zata from loan in January 2020.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Clarke |first1=Fraser |title=Duffy admits he needs to add to his depleted Dumbarton squad |url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/local-news/duffy-admits-needs-add-depleted-21254397 |accessdate=2 February 2020 |work=Daily Record |date=10 January 2020 |location=Glasgow}}</ref> After making just two more appearances for the club, both in January, Zata was released in March 2020 days after the Scottish football season was suspended due to the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|Coronavirus crisis]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dumbartonfootballclub.com/news/?mode=view&id=4344|title=Dumbarton Football Club - MATI ZATA LEAVES DFC|website=www.dumbartonfootballclub.com|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\n\nZata was born in [[Zimbabwe]] but has dual nationality with [[Scotland|Scottish]] and represented Scotland at under-16 level and Zimbabwe at under-23 level. In 2017, Zata represented Scottish National Team Under-16s in a double header match against Switzerland where he played both matches. In March 2019 Zata was called up to represent Zimbabwe Under-23s in the [[African Cup of Nations]] competition. Zata played both matches against [[Mozambique national football team]] earning 2 caps for Zimbabwe.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dundeeunitedfc.co.uk/news/5988/INTERNATIONAL-RECOGNITION-FOR-MATI-ZATA.html|title=INTERNATIONAL RECOGNITION FOR MATI ZATA|website=Dundee United Football Club}}</ref>\n\n== Career statistics ==\n\n{{updated|22:51, 18 January 2020 (UTC)}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|+ Club statistics\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Club\n! rowspan=2 | Season\n! colspan=3 | League\n! colspan=2 | Scottish Cup\n! colspan=2 | League Cup\n! colspan=2 | Other\n! colspan=2 | Total\n|-\n! Division\n! Apps\n! Goals\n! Apps\n! Goals\n! Apps\n! Goals\n! Apps\n! Goals\n! Apps\n! Goals\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]\n|[[2018\u201319 Dundee United F.C. season|2018\u201319]]\n|[[Scottish Championship]]||0||0||0||0||0||0||2||0||2||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!0!!2!!0!!2!!0\n|-\n|[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|[[2019\u201320 Dumbarton F.C. season|2019\u201320]]\n|[[Scottish League One]]\n|3\n|0\n|1\n|0\n|4\n|0\n|1\n|0\n|9\n|0\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" |Career total\n!3