{"title_page": "Conrad Whitby", "text_new": "{{short description|Zimbabwean footballer}}\n{{Orphan|date=October 2019}}\n\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                 = Conrad Whitby\n| image                = \n| caption              = \n| fullname             = Conrad Robert Whitby\n| birth_date           = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1984|5|8}}\n| birth_place          = \n| height               = \n| position             = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub          = [[Wivenhoe Town F.C.|Wivenhoe Town]]\n| clubnumber           = \n| youthyears1          = \n| youthclubs1          = \n| youthyears2          = \n| youthclubs2          = \n| years1               = 2004      | clubs1  = [[Margate F.C.|Margate]]                         | caps1  = 1   | goals1  = 0\n| years2               = 2004      | clubs2  = [[Ramsgate F.C.|Ramsgate]]                       | caps2  = 1   | goals2  = 0\n| years3               = 2004\u20132005 | clubs3  = [[Almondsbury F.C.|Almondsbury]]                 | caps3  =     | goals3  = \n| years4               = 2005\u20132006 | clubs4  = [[Mangotsfield United F.C.|Mangotsfield United]] | caps4  =     | goals4  = \n| years5               = 2006      | clubs5  = [[Bitton F.C.|Bitton]]                           | caps5  =     | goals5  = \n| years6               = 2006      | clubs6  = [[Mangotsfield United F.C.|Mangotsfield United]] | caps6  =     | goals6  = \n| years7               = 2006\u2013200? | clubs7  = [[Keynsham Town F.C.|Keynsham Town]]             | caps7  =     | goals7  = \n| years8               = 2008\u20132009 | clubs8  = [[Motor Action F.C.|Motor Action]]               | caps8  =     | goals8  = \n| years9               = 2010      | clubs9  = [[Eagles F.C. (Zimbabwe)|Eagles]]                | caps9  =     | goals9  = \n| years10              = 2011      | clubs10 = [[Kiglon F.C.|Kiglon]]                           | caps10 =     | goals10 = \n| years11              = 2011      | clubs11 = [[Motor Action F.C.|Motor Action]]               | caps11 =     | goals11 = \n| years12              = 2012      | clubs12 = [[CAPS United F.C.|CAPS United]]                 | caps12 =     | goals12 = \n| years13              = 2012\u2013201? | clubs13 = [[Township Rollers F.C.|Township Rollers]]       | caps13 =     | goals13 = \n| years14              = 201?      | clubs14 = [[Polokwane City F.C.|Polokwane City]]           | caps14 =     | goals14 = \n| years15              = 201?      | clubs15 = [[F.C. Cape Town|FC Cape Town]]                  | caps15 =     | goals15 = \n| years16              = 2014      | clubs16 = [[Wivenhoe Town F.C.|Wivenhoe Town]]             | caps16 = 1   | goals16 = 0\n| nationalyears1       = 2012 | nationalteam1 = [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]] | nationalcaps1 = 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0\n| pcupdate             = \n| ntupdate             = 12:21, 11 December 2014 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Conrad Robert Whitby''' (born 8 May 1984) is a Zimbabwean [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[Wivenhoe Town F.C.|Wivenhoe Town]] of the [[Eastern Counties Football League]] Premier Division.\n\n==Club career==\nWhitby started his career with English club [[Margate F.C.|Margate]], having trialed with them in summer 2003 before signing for the club in January 2004.<ref name=\"Margate history\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.margatefchistory.com/conradwhitby.shtml | title = Conrad Whitby | publisher = Margate FC History | accessdate = 11 December 2014 }}</ref> He went on to make three appearances for Margate, two in the [[Kent Senior Cup]] and one in the [[Conference South]] in the 3\u20133 draw with [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]] on 6 March 2004.<ref name=\"DiggerDagger\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.fansfocus.net/dagenhamandredbridge/index.asp?stid=8324043 | title = Margate Report | publisher = DiggerDagger.com | date = 8 March 2004 | accessdate = 11 December 2014 }}</ref> Whitby subsequently moved on to [[Ramsgate F.C.|Ramsgate]], where he made one appearance in the [[Kent Football League]].<ref name=\"Rams apps\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.ramsgate-fc.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Appearances-2001-2011.pdf | title = Appearances - 2001-2011 | publisher = Ramsgate F.C. | accessdate = 11 December 2014 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20141215031920/http://www.ramsgate-fc.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/Appearances-2001-2011.pdf | archive-date = 15 December 2014 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n\nHe went on to play for [[Mangotsfield United F.C.|Mangotsfield United]], [[Bitton F.C.|Bitton]] and [[Keynsham Town F.C.|Keynsham Town]]. Whilst with Mangotsfield, Whitby served a 35-day suspension.<ref name=\"Hitchin bounce\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.hitchintownfc.co.uk/articles/weekly_articles/EEkVVZylEZlHAUAArx.shtml | title = Hitchin aiming to bounce back in Bristol | publisher = Hitchin Town F.C. | date = 1 September 2005 | accessdate = 11 December 2014 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20150924030538/http://www.hitchintownfc.co.uk/articles/weekly_articles/EEkVVZylEZlHAUAArx.shtml | archive-date = 24 September 2015 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n\nWhitby returned to [[Zimbabwe]] and played for [[Motor Action F.C.|Motor Action]], [[Eagles F.C. (Zimbabwe)|Eagles]], [[Kiglon F.C.|Kiglon]] and [[CAPS United F.C.|CAPS United]] before joining [[Botswana]]n club [[Township Rollers F.C.|Township Rollers]] in 2012.<ref name=\"Chitembwe loses interest in coaching CAPS United\">{{Cite web | url = http://nehandaradio.com/2012/01/05/chitembwe-loses-interest-in-coaching-caps/ | title = Chitembwe loses interest in coaching CAPS United | publisher = Nehanda Radio | date = 5 January 2012 | accessdate = 11 December 2014 }}</ref><ref name=\"FD.eu\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.footballdatabase.eu/football.joueurs.conrad.whitby.156496.en.html | title = Football: Conrad Whitby | publisher = FootballDatabase.eu | accessdate = 11 December 2014 }}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, he signed for [[Eastern Counties Football League]] Premier Division club [[Wivenhoe Town F.C.|Wivenhoe Town]].<ref name=\"Wiv profile\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/wivenhoetownfc/s/the-team-5587.html?player_id=1405968 | title = Conrad Whitby - First Team | publisher = Wivenhoe Town F.C. | accessdate = 11 December 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nWhitby was called up to the [[Zimbabwe national football team]] as a last-minute replacement alongside [[Pardon Chinungwa]], [[Cliff Sekete]], [[Tendai Samanja]], [[Masimba Mambare]] and [[Graham Ncube]] for a friendly against [[Botswana national football team|Botswana]] in January 2012.<ref name=\"Mapeza blasts Zifa\">{{Cite web | url = https://www.newsday.co.zw/2012/01/06/2012-01-06-mapeza-blasts-zifa// | title = Mapeza blasts Zifa | publisher = News Day | date = 6 January 2012 | accessdate = 11 December 2014 }}</ref><ref name=\"Warriors leave for Botswana\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.chronicle.co.zw/warriors-leave-for-botswana/ | title = Warriors leave for Botswana | publisher = The Chronicle | date = 5 January 2012 | accessdate = 11 December 2014 }}</ref><ref name=\"Depleted Warriors hit the road\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.herald.co.zw/depleted-warriors-hit-the-road/ | title = Depleted Warriors hit the road | publisher = The Herald | date = 5 January 2012 | accessdate = 11 December 2014 }}</ref> The games finished a 0\u20130 draw, with Whitby coming on as a substitute.<ref name=\"Players impress Mapeza\">{{Cite web | url = http://www.chronicle.co.zw/players-impress-mapeza/ | title = Players impress Mapeza | publisher = The Chronicle | date = 9 January 2012 | accessdate = 11 December 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nWhitby spent time in [[Thanet District|Thanet]], [[Kent]] as a child and has a British [[passport]].<ref name=\"Margate history\" />\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n*{{NFT player|pid=46268}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Whitby, Conrad}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]